title: Compatible charts

Fix $$r\in\{0,1,\dots,\infty,\omega\}.$$ We say two charts $$(U,\varphi)$$ and $$(V,\psi)$$ for a [[topological manifold|Topologische Mannigfaltigkeit]] are $$\mathcal C^r$$-compatible if the [[transition functions|Kartenwechsel]] $$\psi\circ\varphi^{-1}$$ and $$\varphi\circ\psi^{-1}$$ are $$\mathcal C^r$$-maps (they are then $$\mathcal C^r$$-[[diffeomorphisms|Diffeomorphismus]]).